{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Sometimes you may want to make the cursor jump to a particular control. For instance, when an error message is given, you may want to jump to the field in error, or you may want to skip fields that the user doesn\rquote t ordinarily use when the screen is first presented.\par
\par
You can make the cursor jump to any control at runtime, by using the \cf2 CtrlGoto()\cf1  function.  In this example, the Control name is the same as the field prompt. You can select which control to jump to, and the cursor will jump when you press Start.\par
\par
You can also use CtrlGoto from a child task to jump back to the parent. Press the Child button to see how that works.\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
